    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Analogous to the `prefix` and `suffix` options of `vim.diagnostic.open_float`, it would be great if the `format` callback could return an array of chunks (similar to `nvim_echo`) that specifies highlights for different parts of the text. If a string is returned, `floating_highlight_map[diagnostic.severity]` is applied (current behavior).\r\n\r\nThis would be especially helpful for displaying diagnostics that contain things like diffs where you want to apply different highlighting in the diff to make it easier to read.",
    "closed_at": "2023-01-28T02:09:17Z",
